## 5. Spacing and Layout

### Use Theme Spacing
```typescript
// ✅ Use theme spacing (4px base unit)
sx={{ p: 2 }}    // 8px padding
sx={{ m: 3 }}    // 12px margin
sx={{ px: 4 }}   // 16px horizontal padding
sx={{ py: 1 }}   // 4px vertical padding
```

### Layout with Stack Component
```typescript
// ✅ Use Stack for flexible layouting
<Stack spacing={2} direction="column">
  <Typography variant="title_medium">Title</Typography>
  <Typography variant="body_14_regular">Content</Typography>
</Stack>

// ✅ Responsive Stack layout
<Stack 
  spacing={2} 
  direction={{ xs: 'column', md: 'row' }}
  alignItems="center"
>
  <Button variant="contained">Action 1</Button>
  <Button variant="outlined">Action 2</Button>
</Stack>
```

### Why Use Stack?
- **More flexible** than Box with flex properties
- **Built-in spacing** with `spacing` prop
- **Responsive direction** with breakpoint objects
- **Cleaner code** and better readability
- **Consistent spacing** using theme spacing system

### Responsive Layout
```typescript
// ✅ Use Stack for responsive layouts
<Stack 
  spacing={3}
  direction={{ xs: 'column', md: 'row' }}
  alignItems={{ xs: 'stretch', md: 'center' }}
  justifyContent="space-between"
>
  <Paper elevation={1} sx={{ p: 2, flex: 1 }}>
    Content 1
  </Paper>
  <Paper elevation={1} sx={{ p: 2, flex: 1 }}>
    Content 2
  </Paper>
</Stack>
```

